items.summary: Lez Out: A Benefit Show for the Trans United Front
items.description:
LEZ OUT FEST 11/8

A benefit show for the trans united front @rugclubphl on November 8th. Doors at 5, music at 5:30. Music by @t.ho.mas @ther_ther_ther @isapickett_ and west philly supergroup beef stew (@soupdreamss @cowpokesband@dorthia_aurora as mirror fish) 

DJ set to close the night by @xtradiol

Raffle items from @eemilywilsonn @merlinstempleofdoom the Wagner institute & more

Trans united front (TUF) is a trans affinity group within Philly Socialists. We seek to facilitate connection, mutual aid, and solidarity between interconnected political struggles within the Philadelphia trans community. Funds raised will go towards costs associated with running trans self defense classes, including a space to host and instructors.

Accessibility info:

- MASKS REQUIRED/PROVIDED
- Enter from side alley through backyard. 6 steps down to basement where music is.
- Limited seating in basement, mostly standing. Exceptions made upon request.
- Bathroom is on 1st floor, one flight of stairs up from basement.
- Volume depends on the show, we have free ear plugs. No strobe lights.
- Venue within walking distance from SEPTA routes 13, 34, 11, 36 and 64.

HOPE 2 C U THERE

SOLIDARITY FOREVER

items.description:
Our seasonal convocation of all members, conducted both in-person and online.  Any member in good standing can attend, vote, propose a project/policy or run for an open elected position.
 
Proposal guide: https://cryptpad.fr/doc/#/2/doc/view/aEB-ij7WqdBHe27D8XSvRRxJbnR7e4jyvQnPBf4ZrOo/
 
Our Constitution: https://static1.squarespace.com/static/59cb1893edaed8670cb27244/t/59f7a88d6c319421a027d291/1509402765969/Constitution+--+2017+appoved.pdf 
 
Currently, we have 3 open arbiter positions.
 
Food will be provided, masks will be required and provided.
